Changelog:

Version 3.4.1 (2012-06-04)
 * derive default config file location at 'make' time
 * include vlists in RPM

Version 3.4.0 (2012-05-22)
 * include setup.py, shuffle files around a bit for this
 * update and add a few make targets
 * provide regularly updated vlists on netmeister.org; use those
 * unroll loops in Makefile so this works with gmake
 * default to rh5 and netbsd vlists
 * use relative path to 'yvc' in yvc.php
 * exit '2' if vulnerabilities were found

Version 3.3.0 (2011-12-07)
 * update redhat-oval->yvc converter to handle input as a stream
 * update sample Makefile to include RH6 lists

Version 3.2.0 (2011-04-20)
 * add support for an optional 'severity' field in a vlist

Version 3.1.3 (2011-01-27)
 * properly match exact vulnerability matches

Version 3.1.2 (2010-01-08)
 * fetch-vlist: set PATH to ensure helper tools are found

Version 3.1.1 (2009-11-01)
 * actually do fetch the rh vlists

Version 3.1.0 (2009-11-01)
 * add support for fetching and using vlists for RHEL4 and RHEL5
 * switch to using the yvlist and the correct platform-specific
   vlist by default

Version 3.0.0 (2009-05-03)
 * avoid errors when removing the vlists that haven't been changed
 * switch to using the FreeBSD specific vlist by default and disable
   the NetBSD vlist (though it continues to be fetched)

Version 2.0.5 (2009-02-13)
 * use python2.5 as the shebang, as we're explicitly requiring
   ypython25

Version 2.0.4 (2009-02-13)
 * ensure a single vlist given on the command-line overrides the defaults
   from the config file

Version 2.0.3 (2008-12-09)
 * use ypython25 instead of ypython-2.5
 * set timeout when fetching vlists, try only once
 * add vlists to manifest
 * don't fail installation if we can't fetch all vlists

Version 2.0.2 (2008-08-14)
 * use bugzilla for bug tracking

Version 2.0.1 (2008-07-31)
 * properly match versions specified as foo>=X<=Y
   (previously, only foo>=X<Y would work)
 * better error reporting on unexpected comparison operator

Version 2.0 (2008-07-19)
 * fix usage for fetch-vlist
 * add support for multiple vlists
 * changed config file paramenter from VLIST to VLISTS

Version 1.0 (2008-07-10)
 * don't try to generate the list of packages to check -- accept it
   from the user as command-line arguments or from stdin (or both)
 * also install additional documentation (BUGS, TODO)

Version 0.1 (2008-07-03)
 * Initial version
